191// Specification
192enum SchemaDraft {
193 kDraftUnknown = -1,
194 kDraftNone = 0,
195 kDraft03 = 3,
196 kDraftMin = 4,
197 kDraft04 = 4,
198 kDraft05 = 5,
199 kDraftMax = 5,
200 kDraft06 = 6,
201 kDraft07 = 7,
202 kDraft2019_09 = 8,
203 kDraft2020_12 = 9
204};
205
206enum OpenApiVersion {
207 kVersionUnknown = -1,
208 kVersionNone = 0,
209 kVersionMin = 2,
210 kVersion20 = 2,
211 kVersion30 = 3,
212 kVersionMax = 3,
213 kVersion31 = 4,
214};
215
216struct Specification {
217 Specification(SchemaDraft d) : draft(d), oapi(kVersionNone) {}
218 Specification(OpenApiVersion o) : oapi(o) {
219 if (oapi == kVersion20) draft = kDraft04;
220 else if (oapi == kVersion30) draft = kDraft05;
221 else if (oapi == kVersion31) draft = kDraft2020_12;
222 else draft = kDraft04;
223 }
224 ~Specification() {}
225 bool IsSupported() const {
226 return ((draft >= kDraftMin && draft <= kDraftMax) && ((oapi == kVersionNone) || (oapi >= kVersionMin && oapi <= kVersionMax)));
227 }
228 SchemaDraft draft;
229 OpenApiVersion oapi;
230};

330// Hasher
331
332// For comparison of compound value
333template<typename Encoding, typename Allocator>
334class Hasher {
335public:
336 typedef typename Encoding::Ch Ch;
337
338 Hasher(Allocator* allocator = 0, size_t stackCapacity = kDefaultSize) : stack_(allocator, stackCapacity) {}
339
340 bool Null() { return WriteType(kNullType); }
341 bool Bool(bool b) { return WriteType(b ? kTrueType : kFalseType); }
342 bool Int(int i) { Number n; n.u.i = i; n.d = static_cast<double>(i); return WriteNumber(n); }
343 bool Uint(unsigned u) { Number n; n.u.u = u; n.d = static_cast<double>(u); return WriteNumber(n); }
344 bool Int64(int64_t i) { Number n; n.u.i = i; n.d = static_cast<double>(i); return WriteNumber(n); }
345 bool Uint64(uint64_t u) { Number n; n.u.u = u; n.d = static_cast<double>(u); return WriteNumber(n); }
346 bool Double(double d) {
347 Number n;
348 if (d < 0) n.u.i = static_cast<int64_t>(d);
349 else n.u.u = static_cast<uint64_t>(d);
350 n.d = d;
351 return WriteNumber(n);
352 }
353
354 bool RawNumber(const Ch* str, SizeType len, bool) {
355 WriteBuffer(kNumberType, str, len * sizeof(Ch));
356 return true;
357 }
358
359 bool String(const Ch* str, SizeType len, bool) {
360 WriteBuffer(kStringType, str, len * sizeof(Ch));
361 return true;
362 }
363
364 bool StartObject() { return true; }
365 bool Key(const Ch* str, SizeType len, bool copy) { return String(str, len, copy); }
366 bool EndObject(SizeType memberCount) {
367 uint64_t h = Hash(0, kObjectType);
368 uint64_t* kv = stack_.template Pop<uint64_t>(memberCount * 2);
369 for (SizeType i = 0; i < memberCount; i++)
370 h ^= Hash(kv[i * 2], kv[i * 2 + 1]); // Use xor to achieve member order insensitive
371 *stack_.template Push<uint64_t>() = h;
372 return true;
373 }
374
375 bool StartArray() { return true; }
376 bool EndArray(SizeType elementCount) {
377 uint64_t h = Hash(0, kArrayType);
378 uint64_t* e = stack_.template Pop<uint64_t>(elementCount);
379 for (SizeType i = 0; i < elementCount; i++)
380 h = Hash(h, e[i]); // Use hash to achieve element order sensitive
381 *stack_.template Push<uint64_t>() = h;
382 return true;
383 }
384
385 bool IsValid() const { return stack_.GetSize() == sizeof(uint64_t); }
386
387 uint64_t GetHashCode() const {
388 RAPIDJSON_ASSERT(IsValid());
389 return *stack_.template Top<uint64_t>();
390 }
391
392private:
393 static const size_t kDefaultSize = 256;
394 struct Number {
395 union U {
396 uint64_t u;
397 int64_t i;
398 }u;
399 double d;
400 };
401
402 bool WriteType(Type type) { return WriteBuffer(type, 0, 0); }
403
404 bool WriteNumber(const Number& n) { return WriteBuffer(kNumberType, &n, sizeof(n)); }
405
406 bool WriteBuffer(Type type, const void* data, size_t len) {
407 // FNV-1a from http://isthe.com/chongo/tech/comp/fnv/
408 uint64_t h = Hash(RAPIDJSON_UINT64_C2(0x84222325, 0xcbf29ce4), type);
409 const unsigned char* d = static_cast<const unsigned char*>(data);
410 for (size_t i = 0; i < len; i++)
411 h = Hash(h, d[i]);
412 *stack_.template Push<uint64_t>() = h;
413 return true;
414 }
415
416 static uint64_t Hash(uint64_t h, uint64_t d) {
417 static const uint64_t kPrime = RAPIDJSON_UINT64_C2(0x00000100, 0x000001b3);
418 h ^= d;
419 h *= kPrime;
420 return h;
421 }
422
423 Stack<Allocator> stack_;
424};

427// SchemaValidationContext
428
429template <typename SchemaDocumentType>
430struct SchemaValidationContext {
431 typedef Schema<SchemaDocumentType> SchemaType;
432 typedef ISchemaStateFactory<SchemaType> SchemaValidatorFactoryType;
433 typedef IValidationErrorHandler<SchemaType> ErrorHandlerType;
434 typedef typename SchemaType::ValueType ValueType;
435 typedef typename ValueType::Ch Ch;
436
437 enum PatternValidatorType {
438 kPatternValidatorOnly,
439 kPatternValidatorWithProperty,
440 kPatternValidatorWithAdditionalProperty
441 };
442
443 SchemaValidationContext(SchemaValidatorFactoryType& f, ErrorHandlerType& eh, const SchemaType* s, unsigned fl = 0) :
444 factory(f),
445 error_handler(eh),
446 schema(s),
447 flags(fl),
448 valueSchema(),
449 invalidKeyword(),
450 invalidCode(),
451 hasher(),
452 arrayElementHashCodes(),
453 validators(),
454 validatorCount(),
455 patternPropertiesValidators(),
456 patternPropertiesValidatorCount(),
457 patternPropertiesSchemas(),
458 patternPropertiesSchemaCount(),
459 valuePatternValidatorType(kPatternValidatorOnly),
460 propertyExist(),
461 inArray(false),
462 valueUniqueness(false),
463 arrayUniqueness(false)
464 {
465 }
466
467 ~SchemaValidationContext() {
468 if (hasher)
469 factory.DestroryHasher(hasher);
470 if (validators) {
471 for (SizeType i = 0; i < validatorCount; i++) {
472 if (validators[i]) {
473 factory.DestroySchemaValidator(validators[i]);
474 }
475 }
476 factory.FreeState(validators);
477 }
478 if (patternPropertiesValidators) {
479 for (SizeType i = 0; i < patternPropertiesValidatorCount; i++) {
480 if (patternPropertiesValidators[i]) {
481 factory.DestroySchemaValidator(patternPropertiesValidators[i]);
482 }
483 }
484 factory.FreeState(patternPropertiesValidators);
485 }
486 if (patternPropertiesSchemas)
487 factory.FreeState(patternPropertiesSchemas);
488 if (propertyExist)
489 factory.FreeState(propertyExist);
490 }
491
492 SchemaValidatorFactoryType& factory;
493 ErrorHandlerType& error_handler;
494 const SchemaType* schema;
495 unsigned flags;
496 const SchemaType* valueSchema;
497 const Ch* invalidKeyword;
498 ValidateErrorCode invalidCode;
499 void* hasher; // Only validator access
500 void* arrayElementHashCodes; // Only validator access this
501 ISchemaValidator** validators;
502 SizeType validatorCount;
503 ISchemaValidator** patternPropertiesValidators;
504 SizeType patternPropertiesValidatorCount;
505 const SchemaType** patternPropertiesSchemas;
506 SizeType patternPropertiesSchemaCount;
507 PatternValidatorType valuePatternValidatorType;
508 PatternValidatorType objectPatternValidatorType;
509 SizeType arrayElementIndex;
510 bool* propertyExist;
511 bool inArray;
512 bool valueUniqueness;
513 bool arrayUniqueness;
514};

517// Schema
518
519template <typename SchemaDocumentType>
520class Schema {
521public:
522 typedef typename SchemaDocumentType::ValueType ValueType;
523 typedef typename SchemaDocumentType::AllocatorType AllocatorType;
524 typedef typename SchemaDocumentType::PointerType PointerType;
525 typedef typename ValueType::EncodingType EncodingType;
526 typedef typename EncodingType::Ch Ch;
527 typedef SchemaValidationContext<SchemaDocumentType> Context;
528 typedef Schema<SchemaDocumentType> SchemaType;
529 typedef GenericValue<EncodingType, AllocatorType> SValue;
530 typedef IValidationErrorHandler<Schema> ErrorHandler;
531 typedef GenericUri<ValueType, AllocatorType> UriType;
532 friend class GenericSchemaDocument<ValueType, AllocatorType>;
533
534 Schema(SchemaDocumentType* schemaDocument, const PointerType& p, const ValueType& value, const ValueType& document, AllocatorType* allocator, const UriType& id = UriType()) :
535 allocator_(allocator),
536 uri_(schemaDocument->GetURI(), *allocator),
537 id_(id, allocator),
538 spec_(schemaDocument->GetSpecification()),
539 pointer_(p, allocator),
540 typeless_(schemaDocument->GetTypeless()),
541 enum_(),
542 enumCount_(),
543 not_(),
544 type_((1 << kTotalSchemaType) - 1), // typeless
545 validatorCount_(),
546 notValidatorIndex_(),
547 properties_(),
548 additionalPropertiesSchema_(),
549 patternProperties_(),
550 patternPropertyCount_(),
551 propertyCount_(),
552 minProperties_(),
553 maxProperties_(SizeType(~0)),
554 additionalProperties_(true),
555 hasDependencies_(),
556 hasRequired_(),
557 hasSchemaDependencies_(),
558 additionalItemsSchema_(),
559 itemsList_(),
560 itemsTuple_(),
561 itemsTupleCount_(),
562 minItems_(),
563 maxItems_(SizeType(~0)),
564 additionalItems_(true),
565 uniqueItems_(false),
566 pattern_(),
567 minLength_(0),
568 maxLength_(~SizeType(0)),
569 exclusiveMinimum_(false),
570 exclusiveMaximum_(false),
571 defaultValueLength_(0),
572 readOnly_(false),
573 writeOnly_(false),
574 nullable_(false)
575 {
576 GenericStringBuffer<EncodingType> sb;
577 p.StringifyUriFragment(sb);
578 RAPIDJSON_SCHEMA_PRINT(Method, "Schema::Schema", sb.GetString(), id.GetString());
579
580 typedef typename ValueType::ConstValueIterator ConstValueIterator;
581 typedef typename ValueType::ConstMemberIterator ConstMemberIterator;
582
583 // PR #1393
584 // Early add this Schema and its $ref(s) in schemaDocument's map to avoid infinite
585 // recursion (with recursive schemas), since schemaDocument->getSchema() is always
586 // checked before creating a new one. Don't cache typeless_, though.
587 if (this != typeless_) {
588 typedef typename SchemaDocumentType::SchemaEntry SchemaEntry;
589 SchemaEntry *entry = schemaDocument->schemaMap_.template Push<SchemaEntry>();
590 new (entry) SchemaEntry(pointer_, this, true, allocator_);
591 schemaDocument->AddSchemaRefs(this);
592 }
593
594 if (!value.IsObject())
595 return;
596
597 // If we have an id property, resolve it with the in-scope id
598 // Not supported for open api 2.0 or 3.0
599 if (spec_.oapi != kVersion20 && spec_.oapi != kVersion30)
600 if (const ValueType* v = GetMember(value, GetIdString())) {
601 if (v->IsString()) {
602 UriType local(*v, allocator);
603 id_ = local.Resolve(id_, allocator);
604 RAPIDJSON_SCHEMA_PRINT(SchemaIds, id.GetString(), v->GetString(), id_.GetString());
605 }
606 }
607
608 if (const ValueType* v = GetMember(value, GetTypeString())) {
609 type_ = 0;
610 if (v->IsString())
611 AddType(*v);
612 else if (v->IsArray())
613 for (ConstValueIterator itr = v->Begin(); itr != v->End(); ++itr)
614 AddType(*itr);
615 }
616
617 if (const ValueType* v = GetMember(value, GetEnumString())) {
618 if (v->IsArray() && v->Size() > 0) {
619 enum_ = static_cast<uint64_t*>(allocator_->Malloc(sizeof(uint64_t) * v->Size()));
620 for (ConstValueIterator itr = v->Begin(); itr != v->End(); ++itr) {
621 typedef Hasher<EncodingType, MemoryPoolAllocator<AllocatorType> > EnumHasherType;
622 char buffer[256u + 24];
623 MemoryPoolAllocator<AllocatorType> hasherAllocator(buffer, sizeof(buffer));
624 EnumHasherType h(&hasherAllocator, 256);
625 itr->Accept(h);
626 enum_[enumCount_++] = h.GetHashCode();
627 }
628 }
629 }
630
631 if (schemaDocument)
632 AssignIfExist(allOf_, *schemaDocument, p, value, GetAllOfString(), document);
633
634 // AnyOf, OneOf, Not not supported for open api 2.0
635 if (schemaDocument && spec_.oapi != kVersion20) {
636 AssignIfExist(anyOf_, *schemaDocument, p, value, GetAnyOfString(), document);
637 AssignIfExist(oneOf_, *schemaDocument, p, value, GetOneOfString(), document);
638
639 if (const ValueType* v = GetMember(value, GetNotString())) {
640 schemaDocument->CreateSchema(&not_, p.Append(GetNotString(), allocator_), *v, document, id_);
641 notValidatorIndex_ = validatorCount_;
642 validatorCount_++;
643 }
644 }
645
646 // Object
647
648 const ValueType* properties = GetMember(value, GetPropertiesString());
649 const ValueType* required = GetMember(value, GetRequiredString());
650 const ValueType* dependencies = GetMember(value, GetDependenciesString());
651 {
652 // Gather properties from properties/required/dependencies
653 SValue allProperties(kArrayType);
654
655 if (properties && properties->IsObject())
656 for (ConstMemberIterator itr = properties->MemberBegin(); itr != properties->MemberEnd(); ++itr)
657 AddUniqueElement(allProperties, itr->name);
658
659 if (required && required->IsArray())
660 for (ConstValueIterator itr = required->Begin(); itr != required->End(); ++itr)
661 if (itr->IsString())
662 AddUniqueElement(allProperties, *itr);
663
664 // Dependencies not supported for open api 2.0 and 3.0
665 if (spec_.oapi != kVersion20 && spec_.oapi != kVersion30)
666 if (dependencies && dependencies->IsObject())
667 for (ConstMemberIterator itr = dependencies->MemberBegin(); itr != dependencies->MemberEnd(); ++itr) {
668 AddUniqueElement(allProperties, itr->name);
669 if (itr->value.IsArray())
670 for (ConstValueIterator i = itr->value.Begin(); i != itr->value.End(); ++i)
671 if (i->IsString())
672 AddUniqueElement(allProperties, *i);
673 }
674
675 if (allProperties.Size() > 0) {
676 propertyCount_ = allProperties.Size();
677 properties_ = static_cast<Property*>(allocator_->Malloc(sizeof(Property) * propertyCount_));
678 for (SizeType i = 0; i < propertyCount_; i++) {
679 new (&properties_[i]) Property();
680 properties_[i].name = allProperties[i];
681 properties_[i].schema = typeless_;
682 }
683 }
684 }
685
686 if (properties && properties->IsObject()) {
687 PointerType q = p.Append(GetPropertiesString(), allocator_);
688 for (ConstMemberIterator itr = properties->MemberBegin(); itr != properties->MemberEnd(); ++itr) {
689 SizeType index;
690 if (FindPropertyIndex(itr->name, &index))
691 schemaDocument->CreateSchema(&properties_[index].schema, q.Append(itr->name, allocator_), itr->value, document, id_);
692 }
693 }
694
695 // PatternProperties not supported for open api 2.0 and 3.0
696 if (spec_.oapi != kVersion20 && spec_.oapi != kVersion30)
697 if (const ValueType* v = GetMember(value, GetPatternPropertiesString())) {
698 PointerType q = p.Append(GetPatternPropertiesString(), allocator_);
699 patternProperties_ = static_cast<PatternProperty*>(allocator_->Malloc(sizeof(PatternProperty) * v->MemberCount()));
700 patternPropertyCount_ = 0;
701
702 for (ConstMemberIterator itr = v->MemberBegin(); itr != v->MemberEnd(); ++itr) {
703 new (&patternProperties_[patternPropertyCount_]) PatternProperty();
704 PointerType r = q.Append(itr->name, allocator_);
705 patternProperties_[patternPropertyCount_].pattern = CreatePattern(itr->name, schemaDocument, r);
706 schemaDocument->CreateSchema(&patternProperties_[patternPropertyCount_].schema, r, itr->value, document, id_);
707 patternPropertyCount_++;
708 }
709 }
710
711 if (required && required->IsArray())
712 for (ConstValueIterator itr = required->Begin(); itr != required->End(); ++itr)
713 if (itr->IsString()) {
714 SizeType index;
715 if (FindPropertyIndex(*itr, &index)) {
716 properties_[index].required = true;
717 hasRequired_ = true;
718 }
719 }
720
721 // Dependencies not supported for open api 2.0 and 3.0
722 if (spec_.oapi != kVersion20 && spec_.oapi != kVersion30)
723 if (dependencies && dependencies->IsObject()) {
724 PointerType q = p.Append(GetDependenciesString(), allocator_);
725 hasDependencies_ = true;
726 for (ConstMemberIterator itr = dependencies->MemberBegin(); itr != dependencies->MemberEnd(); ++itr) {
727 SizeType sourceIndex;
728 if (FindPropertyIndex(itr->name, &sourceIndex)) {
729 if (itr->value.IsArray()) {
730 properties_[sourceIndex].dependencies = static_cast<bool*>(allocator_->Malloc(sizeof(bool) * propertyCount_));
731 std::memset(properties_[sourceIndex].dependencies, 0, sizeof(bool)* propertyCount_);
732 for (ConstValueIterator targetItr = itr->value.Begin(); targetItr != itr->value.End(); ++targetItr) {
733 SizeType targetIndex;
734 if (FindPropertyIndex(*targetItr, &targetIndex))
735 properties_[sourceIndex].dependencies[targetIndex] = true;
736 }
737 }
738 else if (itr->value.IsObject()) {
739 hasSchemaDependencies_ = true;
740 schemaDocument->CreateSchema(&properties_[sourceIndex].dependenciesSchema, q.Append(itr->name, allocator_), itr->value, document, id_);
741 properties_[sourceIndex].dependenciesValidatorIndex = validatorCount_;
742 validatorCount_++;
743 }
744 }
745 }
746 }
747
748 if (const ValueType* v = GetMember(value, GetAdditionalPropertiesString())) {
749 if (v->IsBool())
750 additionalProperties_ = v->GetBool();
751 else if (v->IsObject())
752 schemaDocument->CreateSchema(&additionalPropertiesSchema_, p.Append(GetAdditionalPropertiesString(), allocator_), *v, document, id_);
753 }
754
755 AssignIfExist(minProperties_, value, GetMinPropertiesString());
756 AssignIfExist(maxProperties_, value, GetMaxPropertiesString());
757
758 // Array
759 if (const ValueType* v = GetMember(value, GetItemsString())) {
760 PointerType q = p.Append(GetItemsString(), allocator_);
761 if (v->IsObject()) // List validation
762 schemaDocument->CreateSchema(&itemsList_, q, *v, document, id_);
763 else if (v->IsArray()) { // Tuple validation
764 itemsTuple_ = static_cast<const Schema**>(allocator_->Malloc(sizeof(const Schema*) * v->Size()));
765 SizeType index = 0;
766 for (ConstValueIterator itr = v->Begin(); itr != v->End(); ++itr, index++)
767 schemaDocument->CreateSchema(&itemsTuple_[itemsTupleCount_++], q.Append(index, allocator_), *itr, document, id_);
768 }
769 }
770
771 AssignIfExist(minItems_, value, GetMinItemsString());
772 AssignIfExist(maxItems_, value, GetMaxItemsString());
773
774 // AdditionalItems not supported for openapi 2.0 and 3.0
775 if (spec_.oapi != kVersion20 && spec_.oapi != kVersion30)
776 if (const ValueType* v = GetMember(value, GetAdditionalItemsString())) {
777 if (v->IsBool())
778 additionalItems_ = v->GetBool();
779 else if (v->IsObject())
780 schemaDocument->CreateSchema(&additionalItemsSchema_, p.Append(GetAdditionalItemsString(), allocator_), *v, document, id_);
781 }
782
783 AssignIfExist(uniqueItems_, value, GetUniqueItemsString());
784
785 // String
786 AssignIfExist(minLength_, value, GetMinLengthString());
787 AssignIfExist(maxLength_, value, GetMaxLengthString());
788
789 if (const ValueType* v = GetMember(value, GetPatternString()))
790 pattern_ = CreatePattern(*v, schemaDocument, p.Append(GetPatternString(), allocator_));
791
792 // Number
793 if (const ValueType* v = GetMember(value, GetMinimumString()))
794 if (v->IsNumber())
795 minimum_.CopyFrom(*v, *allocator_);
796
797 if (const ValueType* v = GetMember(value, GetMaximumString()))
798 if (v->IsNumber())
799 maximum_.CopyFrom(*v, *allocator_);
800
801 AssignIfExist(exclusiveMinimum_, value, GetExclusiveMinimumString());
802 AssignIfExist(exclusiveMaximum_, value, GetExclusiveMaximumString());
803
804 if (const ValueType* v = GetMember(value, GetMultipleOfString()))
805 if (v->IsNumber() && v->GetDouble() > 0.0)
806 multipleOf_.CopyFrom(*v, *allocator_);
807
808 // Default
809 if (const ValueType* v = GetMember(value, GetDefaultValueString()))
810 if (v->IsString())
811 defaultValueLength_ = v->GetStringLength();
812
813 // ReadOnly - open api only (until draft 7 supported)
814 // WriteOnly - open api 3 only (until draft 7 supported)
815 // Both can't be true
816 if (spec_.oapi != kVersionNone)
817 AssignIfExist(readOnly_, value, GetReadOnlyString());
818 if (spec_.oapi >= kVersion30)
819 AssignIfExist(writeOnly_, value, GetWriteOnlyString());
820 if (readOnly_ && writeOnly_)
821 schemaDocument->SchemaError(kSchemaErrorReadOnlyAndWriteOnly, p);
822
823 // Nullable - open api 3 only
824 // If true add 'null' as allowable type
825 if (spec_.oapi >= kVersion30) {
826 AssignIfExist(nullable_, value, GetNullableString());
827 if (nullable_)
828 AddType(GetNullString());
829 }
830 }
831
832 ~Schema() {
833 AllocatorType::Free(enum_);
834 if (properties_) {
835 for (SizeType i = 0; i < propertyCount_; i++)
836 properties_[i].~Property();
837 AllocatorType::Free(properties_);
838 }
839 if (patternProperties_) {
840 for (SizeType i = 0; i < patternPropertyCount_; i++)
841 patternProperties_[i].~PatternProperty();
842 AllocatorType::Free(patternProperties_);
843 }
844 AllocatorType::Free(itemsTuple_);
845#if RAPIDJSON_SCHEMA_HAS_REGEX
846 if (pattern_) {
847 pattern_->~RegexType();
848 AllocatorType::Free(pattern_);
849 }
850#endif
851 }

868
869 bool BeginValue(Context& context) const {
870 RAPIDJSON_SCHEMA_PRINT(Method, "Schema::BeginValue");
871 if (context.inArray) {
872 if (uniqueItems_)
873 context.valueUniqueness = true;
874
875 if (itemsList_)
876 context.valueSchema = itemsList_;
877 else if (itemsTuple_) {
878 if (context.arrayElementIndex < itemsTupleCount_)
879 context.valueSchema = itemsTuple_[context.arrayElementIndex];
880 else if (additionalItemsSchema_)
881 context.valueSchema = additionalItemsSchema_;
882 else if (additionalItems_)
883 context.valueSchema = typeless_;
884 else {
885 context.error_handler.DisallowedItem(context.arrayElementIndex);
886 // Must set valueSchema for when kValidateContinueOnErrorFlag is set, else reports spurious type error
887 context.valueSchema = typeless_;
888 // Must bump arrayElementIndex for when kValidateContinueOnErrorFlag is set
889 context.arrayElementIndex++;
890 RAPIDJSON_INVALID_KEYWORD_RETURN(kValidateErrorAdditionalItems);
891 }
892 }
893 else
894 context.valueSchema = typeless_;
895
896 context.arrayElementIndex++;
897 }
898 return true;
899 }
900
901 RAPIDJSON_FORCEINLINE bool EndValue(Context& context) const {
902 RAPIDJSON_SCHEMA_PRINT(Method, "Schema::EndValue");
903 // Only check pattern properties if we have validators
904 if (context.patternPropertiesValidatorCount > 0) {
905 bool otherValid = false;
906 SizeType count = context.patternPropertiesValidatorCount;
907 if (context.objectPatternValidatorType != Context::kPatternValidatorOnly)
908 otherValid = context.patternPropertiesValidators[--count]->IsValid();
909
910 bool patternValid = true;
911 for (SizeType i = 0; i < count; i++)
912 if (!context.patternPropertiesValidators[i]->IsValid()) {
913 patternValid = false;
914 break;
915 }
916
917 if (context.objectPatternValidatorType == Context::kPatternValidatorOnly) {
918 if (!patternValid) {
919 context.error_handler.PropertyViolations(context.patternPropertiesValidators, count);
920 RAPIDJSON_INVALID_KEYWORD_RETURN(kValidateErrorPatternProperties);
921 }
922 }
923 else if (context.objectPatternValidatorType == Context::kPatternValidatorWithProperty) {
924 if (!patternValid || !otherValid) {
925 context.error_handler.PropertyViolations(context.patternPropertiesValidators, count + 1);
926 RAPIDJSON_INVALID_KEYWORD_RETURN(kValidateErrorPatternProperties);
927 }
928 }
929 else if (!patternValid && !otherValid) { // kPatternValidatorWithAdditionalProperty)
930 context.error_handler.PropertyViolations(context.patternPropertiesValidators, count + 1);
931 RAPIDJSON_INVALID_KEYWORD_RETURN(kValidateErrorPatternProperties);
932 }
933 }
934
935 // For enums only check if we have a hasher
936 if (enum_ && context.hasher) {
937 const uint64_t h = context.factory.GetHashCode(context.hasher);
938 for (SizeType i = 0; i < enumCount_; i++)
939 if (enum_[i] == h)
940 goto foundEnum;
941 context.error_handler.DisallowedValue(kValidateErrorEnum);
942 RAPIDJSON_INVALID_KEYWORD_RETURN(kValidateErrorEnum);
943 foundEnum:;
944 }
945
946 // Only check allOf etc if we have validators
947 if (context.validatorCount > 0) {
948 if (allOf_.schemas)
949 for (SizeType i = allOf_.begin; i < allOf_.begin + allOf_.count; i++)
950 if (!context.validators[i]->IsValid()) {
951 context.error_handler.NotAllOf(&context.validators[allOf_.begin], allOf_.count);
952 RAPIDJSON_INVALID_KEYWORD_RETURN(kValidateErrorAllOf);
953 }
954
955 if (anyOf_.schemas) {
956 for (SizeType i = anyOf_.begin; i < anyOf_.begin + anyOf_.count; i++)
957 if (context.validators[i]->IsValid())
958 goto foundAny;
959 context.error_handler.NoneOf(&context.validators[anyOf_.begin], anyOf_.count);
960 RAPIDJSON_INVALID_KEYWORD_RETURN(kValidateErrorAnyOf);
961 foundAny:;
962 }
963
964 if (oneOf_.schemas) {
965 bool oneValid = false;
966 SizeType firstMatch = 0;
967 for (SizeType i = oneOf_.begin; i < oneOf_.begin + oneOf_.count; i++)
968 if (context.validators[i]->IsValid()) {
969 if (oneValid) {
970 context.error_handler.MultipleOneOf(firstMatch, i - oneOf_.begin);
971 RAPIDJSON_INVALID_KEYWORD_RETURN(kValidateErrorOneOfMatch);
972 } else {
973 oneValid = true;
974 firstMatch = i - oneOf_.begin;
975 }
976 }
977 if (!oneValid) {
978 context.error_handler.NotOneOf(&context.validators[oneOf_.begin], oneOf_.count);
979 RAPIDJSON_INVALID_KEYWORD_RETURN(kValidateErrorOneOf);
980 }
981 }
982
983 if (not_ && context.validators[notValidatorIndex_]->IsValid()) {
984 context.error_handler.Disallowed();
985 RAPIDJSON_INVALID_KEYWORD_RETURN(kValidateErrorNot);
986 }
987 }
988
989 return true;
990 }

1054
1055 bool String(Context& context, const Ch* str, SizeType length, bool) const {
1056 RAPIDJSON_SCHEMA_PRINT(Method, "Schema::String", str);
1057 if (!(type_ & (1 << kStringSchemaType))) {
1058 DisallowedType(context, GetStringString());
1059 RAPIDJSON_INVALID_KEYWORD_RETURN(kValidateErrorType);
1060 }
1061
1062 if (minLength_ != 0 || maxLength_ != SizeType(~0)) {
1063 SizeType count;
1064 if (internal::CountStringCodePoint<EncodingType>(str, length, &count)) {
1065 if (count < minLength_) {
1066 context.error_handler.TooShort(str, length, minLength_);
1067 RAPIDJSON_INVALID_KEYWORD_RETURN(kValidateErrorMinLength);
1068 }
1069 if (count > maxLength_) {
1070 context.error_handler.TooLong(str, length, maxLength_);
1071 RAPIDJSON_INVALID_KEYWORD_RETURN(kValidateErrorMaxLength);
1072 }
1073 }
1074 }
1075
1076 if (pattern_ && !IsPatternMatch(pattern_, str, length)) {
1077 context.error_handler.DoesNotMatch(str, length);
1078 RAPIDJSON_INVALID_KEYWORD_RETURN(kValidateErrorPattern);
1079 }
1080
1081 return CreateParallelValidator(context);
1082 }
1083
1084 bool StartObject(Context& context) const {
1085 RAPIDJSON_SCHEMA_PRINT(Method, "Schema::StartObject");
1086 if (!(type_ & (1 << kObjectSchemaType))) {
1087 DisallowedType(context, GetObjectString());
1088 RAPIDJSON_INVALID_KEYWORD_RETURN(kValidateErrorType);
1089 }
1090
1091 if (hasDependencies_ || hasRequired_) {
1092 context.propertyExist = static_cast<bool*>(context.factory.MallocState(sizeof(bool) * propertyCount_));
1093 std::memset(context.propertyExist, 0, sizeof(bool) * propertyCount_);
1094 }
1095
1096 if (patternProperties_) { // pre-allocate schema array
1097 SizeType count = patternPropertyCount_ + 1; // extra for valuePatternValidatorType
1098 context.patternPropertiesSchemas = static_cast<const SchemaType**>(context.factory.MallocState(sizeof(const SchemaType*) * count));
1099 context.patternPropertiesSchemaCount = 0;
1100 std::memset(context.patternPropertiesSchemas, 0, sizeof(SchemaType*) * count);
1101 }
1102
1103 return CreateParallelValidator(context);
1104 }
1105
1106 bool Key(Context& context, const Ch* str, SizeType len, bool) const {
1107 RAPIDJSON_SCHEMA_PRINT(Method, "Schema::Key", str);
1108
1109 if (patternProperties_) {
1110 context.patternPropertiesSchemaCount = 0;
1111 for (SizeType i = 0; i < patternPropertyCount_; i++)
1112 if (patternProperties_[i].pattern && IsPatternMatch(patternProperties_[i].pattern, str, len)) {
1113 context.patternPropertiesSchemas[context.patternPropertiesSchemaCount++] = patternProperties_[i].schema;
1114 context.valueSchema = typeless_;
1115 }
1116 }
1117
1118 SizeType index = 0;
1119 if (FindPropertyIndex(ValueType(str, len).Move(), &index)) {
1120 if (context.patternPropertiesSchemaCount > 0) {
1121 context.patternPropertiesSchemas[context.patternPropertiesSchemaCount++] = properties_[index].schema;
1122 context.valueSchema = typeless_;
1123 context.valuePatternValidatorType = Context::kPatternValidatorWithProperty;
1124 }
1125 else
1126 context.valueSchema = properties_[index].schema;
1127
1128 if (context.propertyExist)
1129 context.propertyExist[index] = true;
1130
1131 return true;
1132 }
1133
1134 if (additionalPropertiesSchema_) {
1135 if (context.patternPropertiesSchemaCount > 0) {
1136 context.patternPropertiesSchemas[context.patternPropertiesSchemaCount++] = additionalPropertiesSchema_;
1137 context.valueSchema = typeless_;
1138 context.valuePatternValidatorType = Context::kPatternValidatorWithAdditionalProperty;
1139 }
1140 else
1141 context.valueSchema = additionalPropertiesSchema_;
1142 return true;
1143 }
1144 else if (additionalProperties_) {
1145 context.valueSchema = typeless_;
1146 return true;
1147 }
1148
1149 if (context.patternPropertiesSchemaCount == 0) { // patternProperties are not additional properties
1150 // Must set valueSchema for when kValidateContinueOnErrorFlag is set, else reports spurious type error
1151 context.valueSchema = typeless_;
1152 context.error_handler.DisallowedProperty(str, len);
1153 RAPIDJSON_INVALID_KEYWORD_RETURN(kValidateErrorAdditionalProperties);
1154 }
1155
1156 return true;
1157 }
1158
1159 bool EndObject(Context& context, SizeType memberCount) const {
1160 RAPIDJSON_SCHEMA_PRINT(Method, "Schema::EndObject");
1161 if (hasRequired_) {
1162 context.error_handler.StartMissingProperties();
1163 for (SizeType index = 0; index < propertyCount_; index++)
1164 if (properties_[index].required && !context.propertyExist[index])
1165 if (properties_[index].schema->defaultValueLength_ == 0 )
1166 context.error_handler.AddMissingProperty(properties_[index].name);
1167 if (context.error_handler.EndMissingProperties())
1168 RAPIDJSON_INVALID_KEYWORD_RETURN(kValidateErrorRequired);
1169 }
1170
1171 if (memberCount < minProperties_) {
1172 context.error_handler.TooFewProperties(memberCount, minProperties_);
1173 RAPIDJSON_INVALID_KEYWORD_RETURN(kValidateErrorMinProperties);
1174 }
1175
1176 if (memberCount > maxProperties_) {
1177 context.error_handler.TooManyProperties(memberCount, maxProperties_);
1178 RAPIDJSON_INVALID_KEYWORD_RETURN(kValidateErrorMaxProperties);
1179 }
1180
1181 if (hasDependencies_) {
1182 context.error_handler.StartDependencyErrors();
1183 for (SizeType sourceIndex = 0; sourceIndex < propertyCount_; sourceIndex++) {
1184 const Property& source = properties_[sourceIndex];
1185 if (context.propertyExist[sourceIndex]) {
1186 if (source.dependencies) {
1187 context.error_handler.StartMissingDependentProperties();
1188 for (SizeType targetIndex = 0; targetIndex < propertyCount_; targetIndex++)
1189 if (source.dependencies[targetIndex] && !context.propertyExist[targetIndex])
1190 context.error_handler.AddMissingDependentProperty(properties_[targetIndex].name);
1191 context.error_handler.EndMissingDependentProperties(source.name);
1192 }
1193 else if (source.dependenciesSchema) {
1194 ISchemaValidator* dependenciesValidator = context.validators[source.dependenciesValidatorIndex];
1195 if (!dependenciesValidator->IsValid())
1196 context.error_handler.AddDependencySchemaError(source.name, dependenciesValidator);
1197 }
1198 }
1199 }
1200 if (context.error_handler.EndDependencyErrors())
1201 RAPIDJSON_INVALID_KEYWORD_RETURN(kValidateErrorDependencies);
1202 }
1203
1204 return true;
1205 }

1207 bool StartArray(Context& context) const {
1208 RAPIDJSON_SCHEMA_PRINT(Method, "Schema::StartArray");
1209 context.arrayElementIndex = 0;
1210 context.inArray = true; // Ensure we note that we are in an array
1211
1212 if (!(type_ & (1 << kArraySchemaType))) {
1213 DisallowedType(context, GetArrayString());
1214 RAPIDJSON_INVALID_KEYWORD_RETURN(kValidateErrorType);
1215 }
1216
1217 return CreateParallelValidator(context);
1218 }
1219
1220 bool EndArray(Context& context, SizeType elementCount) const {
1221 RAPIDJSON_SCHEMA_PRINT(Method, "Schema::EndArray");
1222 context.inArray = false;
1223
1224 if (elementCount < minItems_) {
1225 context.error_handler.TooFewItems(elementCount, minItems_);
1226 RAPIDJSON_INVALID_KEYWORD_RETURN(kValidateErrorMinItems);
1227 }
1228
1229 if (elementCount > maxItems_) {
1230 context.error_handler.TooManyItems(elementCount, maxItems_);
1231 RAPIDJSON_INVALID_KEYWORD_RETURN(kValidateErrorMaxItems);
1232 }
1233
1234 return true;
1235 }

1237 static const ValueType& GetValidateErrorKeyword(ValidateErrorCode validateErrorCode) {
1238 switch (validateErrorCode) {
1239 case kValidateErrorMultipleOf: return GetMultipleOfString();
1240 case kValidateErrorMaximum: return GetMaximumString();
1241 case kValidateErrorExclusiveMaximum: return GetMaximumString(); // Same
1242 case kValidateErrorMinimum: return GetMinimumString();
1243 case kValidateErrorExclusiveMinimum: return GetMinimumString(); // Same
1244
1245 case kValidateErrorMaxLength: return GetMaxLengthString();
1246 case kValidateErrorMinLength: return GetMinLengthString();
1247 case kValidateErrorPattern: return GetPatternString();
1248
1249 case kValidateErrorMaxItems: return GetMaxItemsString();
1250 case kValidateErrorMinItems: return GetMinItemsString();
1251 case kValidateErrorUniqueItems: return GetUniqueItemsString();
1252 case kValidateErrorAdditionalItems: return GetAdditionalItemsString();
1253
1254 case kValidateErrorMaxProperties: return GetMaxPropertiesString();
1255 case kValidateErrorMinProperties: return GetMinPropertiesString();
1256 case kValidateErrorRequired: return GetRequiredString();
1257 case kValidateErrorAdditionalProperties: return GetAdditionalPropertiesString();
1258 case kValidateErrorPatternProperties: return GetPatternPropertiesString();
1259 case kValidateErrorDependencies: return GetDependenciesString();
1260
1261 case kValidateErrorEnum: return GetEnumString();
1262 case kValidateErrorType: return GetTypeString();
1263
1264 case kValidateErrorOneOf: return GetOneOfString();
1265 case kValidateErrorOneOfMatch: return GetOneOfString(); // Same
1266 case kValidateErrorAllOf: return GetAllOfString();
1267 case kValidateErrorAnyOf: return GetAnyOfString();
1268 case kValidateErrorNot: return GetNotString();
1269
1270 case kValidateErrorReadOnly: return GetReadOnlyString();
1271 case kValidateErrorWriteOnly: return GetWriteOnlyString();
1272
1273 default: return GetNullString();
1274 }
1275 }

1278 // Generate functions for string literal according to Ch
1279#define RAPIDJSON_STRING_(name, ...) \
1280 static const ValueType& Get##name##String() {\
1281 static const Ch s[] = { __VA_ARGS__, '\0' };\
1282 static const ValueType v(s, static_cast<SizeType>(sizeof(s) / sizeof(Ch) - 1));\
1283 return v;\
1284 }
1285
1286 RAPIDJSON_STRING_(Null, 'n', 'u', 'l', 'l')
1287 RAPIDJSON_STRING_(Boolean, 'b', 'o', 'o', 'l', 'e', 'a', 'n')
1288 RAPIDJSON_STRING_(Object, 'o', 'b', 'j', 'e', 'c', 't')
1289 RAPIDJSON_STRING_(Array, 'a', 'r', 'r', 'a', 'y')
1290 RAPIDJSON_STRING_(String, 's', 't', 'r', 'i', 'n', 'g')
1291 RAPIDJSON_STRING_(Number, 'n', 'u', 'm', 'b', 'e', 'r')
1292 RAPIDJSON_STRING_(Integer, 'i', 'n', 't', 'e', 'g', 'e', 'r')
1293 RAPIDJSON_STRING_(Type, 't', 'y', 'p', 'e')
1294 RAPIDJSON_STRING_(Enum, 'e', 'n', 'u', 'm')
1295 RAPIDJSON_STRING_(AllOf, 'a', 'l', 'l', 'O', 'f')
1296 RAPIDJSON_STRING_(AnyOf, 'a', 'n', 'y', 'O', 'f')
1297 RAPIDJSON_STRING_(OneOf, 'o', 'n', 'e', 'O', 'f')

1359 template <typename V1, typename V2>
1360 void AddUniqueElement(V1& a, const V2& v) {
1361 for (typename V1::ConstValueIterator itr = a.Begin(); itr != a.End(); ++itr)
1362 if (*itr == v)
1363 return;
1364 V1 c(v, *allocator_);
1365 a.PushBack(c, *allocator_);
1366 }

1368 static const ValueType* GetMember(const ValueType& value, const ValueType& name) {
1369 typename ValueType::ConstMemberIterator itr = value.FindMember(name);
1370 return itr != value.MemberEnd() ? &(itr->value) : 0;
1371 }
1372
1373 static void AssignIfExist(bool& out, const ValueType& value, const ValueType& name) {
1374 if (const ValueType* v = GetMember(value, name))
1375 if (v->IsBool())
1376 out = v->GetBool();
1377 }
1378
1379 static void AssignIfExist(SizeType& out, const ValueType& value, const ValueType& name) {
1380 if (const ValueType* v = GetMember(value, name))
1381 if (v->IsUint64() && v->GetUint64() <= SizeType(~0))
1382 out = static_cast<SizeType>(v->GetUint64());
1383 }
1384
1385 void AssignIfExist(SchemaArray& out, SchemaDocumentType& schemaDocument, const PointerType& p, const ValueType& value, const ValueType& name, const ValueType& document) {
1386 if (const ValueType* v = GetMember(value, name)) {
1387 if (v->IsArray() && v->Size() > 0) {
1388 PointerType q = p.Append(name, allocator_);
1389 out.count = v->Size();
1390 out.schemas = static_cast<const Schema**>(allocator_->Malloc(out.count * sizeof(const Schema*)));
1391 memset(out.schemas, 0, sizeof(Schema*)* out.count);
1392 for (SizeType i = 0; i < out.count; i++)
1393 schemaDocument.CreateSchema(&out.schemas[i], q.Append(i, allocator_), (*v)[i], document, id_);
1394 out.begin = validatorCount_;
1395 validatorCount_ += out.count;
1396 }
1397 }
1398 }

1400#if RAPIDJSON_SCHEMA_USE_INTERNALREGEX
1401 template <typename ValueType>
1402 RegexType* CreatePattern(const ValueType& value, SchemaDocumentType* sd, const PointerType& p) {
1403 if (value.IsString()) {
1404 RegexType* r = new (allocator_->Malloc(sizeof(RegexType))) RegexType(value.GetString(), allocator_);
1405 if (!r->IsValid()) {
1406 sd->SchemaErrorValue(kSchemaErrorRegexInvalid, p, value.GetString(), value.GetStringLength());
1407 r->~RegexType();
1408 AllocatorType::Free(r);
1409 r = 0;
1410 }
1411 return r;
1412 }
1413 return 0;
1414 }
1415
1416 static bool IsPatternMatch(const RegexType* pattern, const Ch *str, SizeType) {
1417 GenericRegexSearch<RegexType> rs(*pattern);
1418 return rs.Search(str);
1419 }
1420#elif RAPIDJSON_SCHEMA_USE_STDREGEX
1421 template <typename ValueType>
1422 RegexType* CreatePattern(const ValueType& value, SchemaDocumentType* sd, const PointerType& p) {
1423 if (value.IsString()) {
1424 RegexType *r = static_cast<RegexType*>(allocator_->Malloc(sizeof(RegexType)));
1425 try {
1426 return new (r) RegexType(value.GetString(), std::size_t(value.GetStringLength()), std::regex_constants::ECMAScript);
1427 }
1428 catch (const std::regex_error& e) {
1429 sd->SchemaErrorValue(kSchemaErrorRegexInvalid, p, value.GetString(), value.GetStringLength());
1430 AllocatorType::Free(r);
1431 }
1432 }
1433 return 0;
1434 }

1436 static bool IsPatternMatch(const RegexType* pattern, const Ch *str, SizeType length) {
1437 std::match_results<const Ch*> r;
1438 return std::regex_search(str, str + length, r, *pattern);
1439 }
1440#else
1441 template <typename ValueType>
1442 RegexType* CreatePattern(const ValueType&) {
1443 return 0;
1444 }

1446 static bool IsPatternMatch(const RegexType*, const Ch *, SizeType) { return true; }

1449 void AddType(const ValueType& type) {
1450 if (type == GetNullString() ) type_ |= 1 << kNullSchemaType;
1451 else if (type == GetBooleanString()) type_ |= 1 << kBooleanSchemaType;
1452 else if (type == GetObjectString() ) type_ |= 1 << kObjectSchemaType;
1453 else if (type == GetArrayString() ) type_ |= 1 << kArraySchemaType;
1454 else if (type == GetStringString() ) type_ |= 1 << kStringSchemaType;
1455 else if (type == GetIntegerString()) type_ |= 1 << kIntegerSchemaType;
1456 else if (type == GetNumberString() ) type_ |= (1 << kNumberSchemaType) | (1 << kIntegerSchemaType);
1457 }
1458
1459 // Creates parallel validators for allOf, anyOf, oneOf, not and schema dependencies, if required.
1460 // Also creates a hasher for enums and array uniqueness, if required.
1461 // Also a useful place to add type-independent error checks.
1462 bool CreateParallelValidator(Context& context) const {
1463 if (enum_ || context.arrayUniqueness)
1464 context.hasher = context.factory.CreateHasher();
1465
1466 if (validatorCount_) {
1467 RAPIDJSON_ASSERT(context.validators == 0);
1468 context.validators = static_cast<ISchemaValidator**>(context.factory.MallocState(sizeof(ISchemaValidator*) * validatorCount_));
1469 std::memset(context.validators, 0, sizeof(ISchemaValidator*) * validatorCount_);
1470 context.validatorCount = validatorCount_;
1471
1472 // Always return after first failure for these sub-validators
1473 if (allOf_.schemas)
1474 CreateSchemaValidators(context, allOf_, false);
1475
1476 if (anyOf_.schemas)
1477 CreateSchemaValidators(context, anyOf_, false);
1478
1479 if (oneOf_.schemas)
1480 CreateSchemaValidators(context, oneOf_, false);
1481
1482 if (not_)
1483 context.validators[notValidatorIndex_] = context.factory.CreateSchemaValidator(*not_, false);
1484
1485 if (hasSchemaDependencies_) {
1486 for (SizeType i = 0; i < propertyCount_; i++)
1487 if (properties_[i].dependenciesSchema)
1488 context.validators[properties_[i].dependenciesValidatorIndex] = context.factory.CreateSchemaValidator(*properties_[i].dependenciesSchema, false);
1489 }
1490 }
1491
1492 // Add any other type-independent checks here
1493 if (readOnly_ && (context.flags & kValidateWriteFlag)) {
1494 context.error_handler.DisallowedWhenWriting();
1495 RAPIDJSON_INVALID_KEYWORD_RETURN(kValidateErrorReadOnly);
1496 }
1497 if (writeOnly_ && (context.flags & kValidateReadFlag)) {
1498 context.error_handler.DisallowedWhenReading();
1499 RAPIDJSON_INVALID_KEYWORD_RETURN(kValidateErrorWriteOnly);
1500 }
1501
1502 return true;
1503 }
1504
1505 void CreateSchemaValidators(Context& context, const SchemaArray& schemas, const bool inheritContinueOnErrors) const {
1506 for (SizeType i = 0; i < schemas.count; i++)
1507 context.validators[schemas.begin + i] = context.factory.CreateSchemaValidator(*schemas.schemas[i], inheritContinueOnErrors);
1508 }

1510 // O(n)
1511 bool FindPropertyIndex(const ValueType& name, SizeType* outIndex) const {
1512 SizeType len = name.GetStringLength();
1513 const Ch* str = name.GetString();
1514 for (SizeType index = 0; index < propertyCount_; index++)
1515 if (properties_[index].name.GetStringLength() == len &&
1516 (std::memcmp(properties_[index].name.GetString(), str, sizeof(Ch) * len) == 0))
1517 {
1518 *outIndex = index;
1519 return true;
1520 }
1521 return false;
1522 }

1524 bool CheckBool(Context& context, bool) const {
1525 if (!(type_ & (1 << kBooleanSchemaType))) {
1526 DisallowedType(context, GetBooleanString());
1527 RAPIDJSON_INVALID_KEYWORD_RETURN(kValidateErrorType);
1528 }
1529 return true;
1530 }
1531
1532 bool CheckInt(Context& context, int64_t i) const {
1533 if (!(type_ & ((1 << kIntegerSchemaType) | (1 << kNumberSchemaType)))) {
1534 DisallowedType(context, GetIntegerString());
1535 RAPIDJSON_INVALID_KEYWORD_RETURN(kValidateErrorType);
1536 }
1537
1538 if (!minimum_.IsNull()) {
1539 if (minimum_.IsInt64()) {
1540 if (exclusiveMinimum_ ? i <= minimum_.GetInt64() : i < minimum_.GetInt64()) {
1541 context.error_handler.BelowMinimum(i, minimum_, exclusiveMinimum_);
1542 RAPIDJSON_INVALID_KEYWORD_RETURN(exclusiveMinimum_ ? kValidateErrorExclusiveMinimum : kValidateErrorMinimum);
1543 }
1544 }
1545 else if (minimum_.IsUint64()) {
1546 context.error_handler.BelowMinimum(i, minimum_, exclusiveMinimum_);
1547 RAPIDJSON_INVALID_KEYWORD_RETURN(exclusiveMinimum_ ? kValidateErrorExclusiveMinimum : kValidateErrorMinimum); // i <= max(int64_t) < minimum.GetUint64()
1548 }
1549 else if (!CheckDoubleMinimum(context, static_cast<double>(i)))
1550 return false;
1551 }
1552
1553 if (!maximum_.IsNull()) {
1554 if (maximum_.IsInt64()) {
1555 if (exclusiveMaximum_ ? i >= maximum_.GetInt64() : i > maximum_.GetInt64()) {
1556 context.error_handler.AboveMaximum(i, maximum_, exclusiveMaximum_);
1557 RAPIDJSON_INVALID_KEYWORD_RETURN(exclusiveMaximum_ ? kValidateErrorExclusiveMaximum : kValidateErrorMaximum);
1558 }
1559 }
1560 else if (maximum_.IsUint64()) { }
1561 /* do nothing */ // i <= max(int64_t) < maximum_.GetUint64()
1562 else if (!CheckDoubleMaximum(context, static_cast<double>(i)))
1563 return false;
1564 }
1565
1566 if (!multipleOf_.IsNull()) {
1567 if (multipleOf_.IsUint64()) {
1568 if (static_cast<uint64_t>(i >= 0 ? i : -i) % multipleOf_.GetUint64() != 0) {
1569 context.error_handler.NotMultipleOf(i, multipleOf_);
1570 RAPIDJSON_INVALID_KEYWORD_RETURN(kValidateErrorMultipleOf);
1571 }
1572 }
1573 else if (!CheckDoubleMultipleOf(context, static_cast<double>(i)))
1574 return false;
1575 }
1576
1577 return true;
1578 }
1579
1580 bool CheckUint(Context& context, uint64_t i) const {
1581 if (!(type_ & ((1 << kIntegerSchemaType) | (1 << kNumberSchemaType)))) {
1582 DisallowedType(context, GetIntegerString());
1583 RAPIDJSON_INVALID_KEYWORD_RETURN(kValidateErrorType);
1584 }
1585
1586 if (!minimum_.IsNull()) {
1587 if (minimum_.IsUint64()) {
1588 if (exclusiveMinimum_ ? i <= minimum_.GetUint64() : i < minimum_.GetUint64()) {
1589 context.error_handler.BelowMinimum(i, minimum_, exclusiveMinimum_);
1590 RAPIDJSON_INVALID_KEYWORD_RETURN(exclusiveMinimum_ ? kValidateErrorExclusiveMinimum : kValidateErrorMinimum);
1591 }
1592 }
1593 else if (minimum_.IsInt64())
1594 /* do nothing */; // i >= 0 > minimum.Getint64()
1595 else if (!CheckDoubleMinimum(context, static_cast<double>(i)))
1596 return false;
1597 }
1598
1599 if (!maximum_.IsNull()) {
1600 if (maximum_.IsUint64()) {
1601 if (exclusiveMaximum_ ? i >= maximum_.GetUint64() : i > maximum_.GetUint64()) {
1602 context.error_handler.AboveMaximum(i, maximum_, exclusiveMaximum_);
1603 RAPIDJSON_INVALID_KEYWORD_RETURN(exclusiveMaximum_ ? kValidateErrorExclusiveMaximum : kValidateErrorMaximum);
1604 }
1605 }
1606 else if (maximum_.IsInt64()) {
1607 context.error_handler.AboveMaximum(i, maximum_, exclusiveMaximum_);
1608 RAPIDJSON_INVALID_KEYWORD_RETURN(exclusiveMaximum_ ? kValidateErrorExclusiveMaximum : kValidateErrorMaximum); // i >= 0 > maximum_
1609 }
1610 else if (!CheckDoubleMaximum(context, static_cast<double>(i)))
1611 return false;
1612 }
1613
1614 if (!multipleOf_.IsNull()) {
1615 if (multipleOf_.IsUint64()) {
1616 if (i % multipleOf_.GetUint64() != 0) {
1617 context.error_handler.NotMultipleOf(i, multipleOf_);
1618 RAPIDJSON_INVALID_KEYWORD_RETURN(kValidateErrorMultipleOf);
1619 }
1620 }
1621 else if (!CheckDoubleMultipleOf(context, static_cast<double>(i)))
1622 return false;
1623 }
1624
1625 return true;
1626 }
1627
1628 bool CheckDoubleMinimum(Context& context, double d) const {
1629 if (exclusiveMinimum_ ? d <= minimum_.GetDouble() : d < minimum_.GetDouble()) {
1630 context.error_handler.BelowMinimum(d, minimum_, exclusiveMinimum_);
1631 RAPIDJSON_INVALID_KEYWORD_RETURN(exclusiveMinimum_ ? kValidateErrorExclusiveMinimum : kValidateErrorMinimum);
1632 }
1633 return true;
1634 }
1635
1636 bool CheckDoubleMaximum(Context& context, double d) const {
1637 if (exclusiveMaximum_ ? d >= maximum_.GetDouble() : d > maximum_.GetDouble()) {
1638 context.error_handler.AboveMaximum(d, maximum_, exclusiveMaximum_);
1639 RAPIDJSON_INVALID_KEYWORD_RETURN(exclusiveMaximum_ ? kValidateErrorExclusiveMaximum : kValidateErrorMaximum);
1640 }
1641 return true;
1642 }
1643
1644 bool CheckDoubleMultipleOf(Context& context, double d) const {
1645 double a = std::abs(d), b = std::abs(multipleOf_.GetDouble());
1646 double q = std::floor(a / b);
1647 double r = a - q * b;
1648 if (r > 0.0) {
1649 context.error_handler.NotMultipleOf(d, multipleOf_);
1650 RAPIDJSON_INVALID_KEYWORD_RETURN(kValidateErrorMultipleOf);
1651 }
1652 return true;
1653 }
1654
1655 void DisallowedType(Context& context, const ValueType& actualType) const {
1656 ErrorHandler& eh = context.error_handler;
1657 eh.StartDisallowedType();
1658
1659 if (type_ & (1 << kNullSchemaType)) eh.AddExpectedType(GetNullString());
1660 if (type_ & (1 << kBooleanSchemaType)) eh.AddExpectedType(GetBooleanString());
1661 if (type_ & (1 << kObjectSchemaType)) eh.AddExpectedType(GetObjectString());
1662 if (type_ & (1 << kArraySchemaType)) eh.AddExpectedType(GetArrayString());
1663 if (type_ & (1 << kStringSchemaType)) eh.AddExpectedType(GetStringString());
1664
1665 if (type_ & (1 << kNumberSchemaType)) eh.AddExpectedType(GetNumberString());
1666 else if (type_ & (1 << kIntegerSchemaType)) eh.AddExpectedType(GetIntegerString());
1667
1668 eh.EndDisallowedType(actualType);
1669 }

1748template<typename Stack, typename Ch>
1749struct TokenHelper {
1750 RAPIDJSON_FORCEINLINE static void AppendIndexToken(Stack& documentStack, SizeType index) {
1751 *documentStack.template Push<Ch>() = '/';
1752 char buffer[21];
1753 size_t length = static_cast<size_t>((sizeof(SizeType) == 4 ? u32toa(index, buffer) : u64toa(index, buffer)) - buffer);
1754 for (size_t i = 0; i < length; i++)
1755 *documentStack.template Push<Ch>() = static_cast<Ch>(buffer[i]);
1756 }
1757};
1758
1759// Partial specialized version for char to prevent buffer copying.
1760template <typename Stack>
1761struct TokenHelper<Stack, char> {
1762 RAPIDJSON_FORCEINLINE static void AppendIndexToken(Stack& documentStack, SizeType index) {
1763 if (sizeof(SizeType) == 4) {
1764 char *buffer = documentStack.template Push<char>(1 + 10); // '/' + uint
1765 *buffer++ = '/';
1766 const char* end = internal::u32toa(index, buffer);
1767 documentStack.template Pop<char>(static_cast<size_t>(10 - (end - buffer)));
1768 }
1769 else {
1770 char *buffer = documentStack.template Push<char>(1 + 20); // '/' + uint64
1771 *buffer++ = '/';
1772 const char* end = internal::u64toa(index, buffer);
1773 documentStack.template Pop<char>(static_cast<size_t>(20 - (end - buffer)));
1774 }
1775 }
1776};

1829
1831
1842 explicit GenericSchemaDocument(const ValueType& document, const Ch* uri = 0, SizeType uriLength = 0,
1843 IRemoteSchemaDocumentProviderType* remoteProvider = 0, Allocator* allocator = 0,
1844 const PointerType& pointer = PointerType(), // PR #1393
1845 const Specification& spec = Specification(kDraft04)) :
1846 remoteProvider_(remoteProvider),
1847 allocator_(allocator),
1848 ownAllocator_(),
1849 root_(),
1850 typeless_(),
1851 schemaMap_(allocator, kInitialSchemaMapSize),
1852 schemaRef_(allocator, kInitialSchemaRefSize),
1853 spec_(spec),
1854 error_(kObjectType),
1855 currentError_()
1856 {
1857 RAPIDJSON_SCHEMA_PRINT(Method, "GenericSchemaDocument::GenericSchemaDocument");
1858 if (!allocator_)
1859 ownAllocator_ = allocator_ = RAPIDJSON_NEW(Allocator)();
1860
1861 Ch noUri[1] = {0};
1862 uri_.SetString(uri ? uri : noUri, uriLength, *allocator_);
1863 docId_ = UriType(uri_, allocator_);
1864
1865 typeless_ = static_cast<SchemaType*>(allocator_->Malloc(sizeof(SchemaType)));
1866 new (typeless_) SchemaType(this, PointerType(), ValueType(kObjectType).Move(), ValueType(kObjectType).Move(), allocator_, docId_);
1867
1868 // Establish the schema draft or open api version.
1869 // We only ever look for '$schema' or 'swagger' or 'openapi' at the root of the document.
1870 SetSchemaSpecification(document);
1871
1872 // Generate root schema, it will call CreateSchema() to create sub-schemas,
1873 // And call HandleRefSchema() if there are $ref.
1874 // PR #1393 use input pointer if supplied
1875 root_ = typeless_;
1876 if (pointer.GetTokenCount() == 0) {
1877 CreateSchemaRecursive(&root_, pointer, document, document, docId_);
1878 }
1879 else if (const ValueType* v = pointer.Get(document)) {
1880 CreateSchema(&root_, pointer, *v, document, docId_);
1881 }
1882 else {
1883 GenericStringBuffer<EncodingType> sb;
1884 pointer.StringifyUriFragment(sb);
1885 SchemaErrorValue(kSchemaErrorStartUnknown, PointerType(), sb.GetString(), static_cast<SizeType>(sb.GetSize() / sizeof(Ch)));
1886 }
1887
1888 RAPIDJSON_ASSERT(root_ != 0);
1889
1890 schemaRef_.ShrinkToFit(); // Deallocate all memory for ref
1891 }

2079 static SchemaDraft GetSchemaDraft(const ValueType& document) {
2080 static const Ch kDraft03String[] = { 'h', 't', 't', 'p', ':', '/', '/', 'j', 's', 'o', 'n', '-', 's', 'c', 'h', 'e', 'm', 'a', '.', 'o', 'r', 'g', '/', 'd', 'r', 'a', 'f', 't', '-', '0', '3', '/', 's', 'c', 'h', 'e', 'm', 'a', '#', '\0' };

2082 static const Ch kDraft05String[] = { 'h', 't', 't', 'p', ':', '/', '/', 'j', 's', 'o', 'n', '-', 's', 'c', 'h', 'e', 'm', 'a', '.', 'o', 'r', 'g', '/', 'd', 'r', 'a', 'f', 't', '-', '0', '5', '/', 's', 'c', 'h', 'e', 'm', 'a', '#', '\0' };

2085 static const Ch kDraft2019_09String[] = { 'h', 't', 't', 'p', 's', ':', '/', '/', 'j', 's', 'o', 'n', '-', 's', 'c', 'h', 'e', 'm', 'a', '.', 'o', 'r', 'g', '/', 'd', 'r', 'a', 'f', 't', '/', '2', '0', '1', '9', '-', '0', '9', '/', 's', 'c', 'h', 'e', 'm', 'a', '\0' };
2086 static const Ch kDraft2020_12String[] = { 'h', 't', 't', 'p', 's', ':', '/', '/', 'j', 's', 'o', 'n', '-', 's', 'c', 'h', 'e', 'm', 'a', '.', 'o', 'r', 'g', '/', 'd', 'r', 'a', 'f', 't', '/', '2', '0', '2', '0', '-', '1', '2', '/', 's', 'c', 'h', 'e', 'm', 'a', '\0' };
2087
2088 if (!document.IsObject()) {
2089 return kDraftNone;
2090 }
2091
2092 // Get the schema draft from the $schema keyword at the supplied location
2093 typename ValueType::ConstMemberIterator itr = document.FindMember(SchemaType::GetSchemaString());
2094 if (itr != document.MemberEnd()) {
2095 if (!itr->value.IsString()) return kDraftUnknown;
2096 const UriType draftUri(itr->value);
2097 // Check base uri for match
2098 if (draftUri.Match(UriType(kDraft04String), false)) return kDraft04;
2099 if (draftUri.Match(UriType(kDraft05String), false)) return kDraft05;
2100 if (draftUri.Match(UriType(kDraft06String), false)) return kDraft06;
2101 if (draftUri.Match(UriType(kDraft07String), false)) return kDraft07;
2102 if (draftUri.Match(UriType(kDraft03String), false)) return kDraft03;
2103 if (draftUri.Match(UriType(kDraft2019_09String), false)) return kDraft2019_09;
2104 if (draftUri.Match(UriType(kDraft2020_12String), false)) return kDraft2020_12;
2105 return kDraftUnknown;
2106 }
2107 // $schema not found
2108 return kDraftNone;

2112 // Get open api version of any schema document
2113 static OpenApiVersion GetOpenApiVersion(const ValueType& document) {
2114 static const Ch kVersion20String[] = { '2', '.', '0', '\0' };
2115 static const Ch kVersion30String[] = { '3', '.', '0', '.', '\0' }; // ignore patch level
2116 static const Ch kVersion31String[] = { '3', '.', '1', '.', '\0' }; // ignore patch level
2117 static SizeType len = internal::StrLen<Ch>(kVersion30String);
2118
2119 if (!document.IsObject()) {
2120 return kVersionNone;
2121 }
2122
2123 // Get the open api version from the swagger / openapi keyword at the supplied location
2124 typename ValueType::ConstMemberIterator itr = document.FindMember(SchemaType::GetSwaggerString());
2125 if (itr == document.MemberEnd()) itr = document.FindMember(SchemaType::GetOpenApiString());
2126 if (itr != document.MemberEnd()) {
2127 if (!itr->value.IsString()) return kVersionUnknown;
2128 const ValueType kVersion20Value(kVersion20String);
2129 if (kVersion20Value == itr->value) return kVersion20; // must match 2.0 exactly
2130 const ValueType kVersion30Value(kVersion30String);
2131 if (itr->value.GetStringLength() > len && kVersion30Value == ValueType(itr->value.GetString(), len)) return kVersion30; // must match 3.0.x
2132 const ValueType kVersion31Value(kVersion31String);
2133 if (itr->value.GetStringLength() > len && kVersion31Value == ValueType(itr->value.GetString(), len)) return kVersion31; // must match 3.1.x
2134 return kVersionUnknown;
2135 }
2136 // swagger or openapi not found
2137 return kVersionNone;
2138 }

2140 // Get the draft of the schema or the open api version (which implies the draft).
2141 // Report an error if schema draft or open api version not supported or not recognized, or both in document, and carry on.
2142 void SetSchemaSpecification(const ValueType& document) {
2143 // Look for '$schema', 'swagger' or 'openapi' keyword at document root
2144 SchemaDraft docDraft = GetSchemaDraft(document);
2145 OpenApiVersion docOapi = GetOpenApiVersion(document);
2146 // Error if both in document
2147 if (docDraft != kDraftNone && docOapi != kVersionNone)
2148 SchemaError(kSchemaErrorSpecIllegal, PointerType());
2149 // Use document draft or open api version if present or use spec from constructor
2150 if (docDraft != kDraftNone)
2151 spec_ = Specification(docDraft);
2152 else if (docOapi != kVersionNone)
2153 spec_ = Specification(docOapi);
2154 // Error if draft or version unknown
2155 if (spec_.draft == kDraftUnknown || spec_.oapi == kVersionUnknown)
2156 SchemaError(kSchemaErrorSpecUnknown, PointerType());
2157 else if (!spec_.IsSupported())
2158 SchemaError(kSchemaErrorSpecUnsupported, PointerType());
2159 }

2202 // Changed by PR #1393
2203 // TODO should this return a UriType& ?
2204 bool HandleRefSchema(const PointerType& source, const SchemaType** schema, const ValueType& v, const ValueType& document, const UriType& id) {
2205 typename ValueType::ConstMemberIterator itr = v.FindMember(SchemaType::GetRefString());
2206 if (itr == v.MemberEnd())
2207 return false;
2208
2209 GenericStringBuffer<EncodingType> sb;
2210 source.StringifyUriFragment(sb);
2211 RAPIDJSON_SCHEMA_PRINT(Method, "GenericSchemaDocument::HandleRefSchema", sb.GetString(), id.GetString());
2212 // Resolve the source pointer to the $ref'ed schema (finally)
2213 new (schemaRef_.template Push<SchemaRefPtr>()) SchemaRefPtr(&source);
2214
2215 if (itr->value.IsString()) {
2216 SizeType len = itr->value.GetStringLength();
2217 if (len == 0)
2218 SchemaError(kSchemaErrorRefInvalid, source);
2219 else {
2220 // First resolve $ref against the in-scope id
2221 UriType scopeId = UriType(id, allocator_);
2222 UriType ref = UriType(itr->value, allocator_).Resolve(scopeId, allocator_);
2223 RAPIDJSON_SCHEMA_PRINT(SchemaIds, id.GetString(), itr->value.GetString(), ref.GetString());
2224 // See if the resolved $ref minus the fragment matches a resolved id in this document
2225 // Search from the root. Returns the subschema in the document and its absolute JSON pointer.
2226 PointerType basePointer = PointerType();
2227 const ValueType *base = FindId(document, ref, basePointer, docId_, false);
2228 if (!base) {
2229 // Remote reference - call the remote document provider
2230 if (!remoteProvider_)
2231 SchemaError(kSchemaErrorRefNoRemoteProvider, source);
2232 else {
2233 if (const GenericSchemaDocument* remoteDocument = remoteProvider_->GetRemoteDocument(ref, spec_)) {
2234 const Ch* s = ref.GetFragString();
2235 len = ref.GetFragStringLength();
2236 if (len <= 1 || s[1] == '/') {
2237 // JSON pointer fragment, absolute in the remote schema
2238 const PointerType pointer(s, len, allocator_);
2239 if (!pointer.IsValid())
2240 SchemaErrorPointer(kSchemaErrorRefPointerInvalid, source, s, len, pointer);
2241 else {
2242 // Get the subschema
2243 if (const SchemaType *sc = remoteDocument->GetSchema(pointer)) {
2244 if (schema)
2245 *schema = sc;
2246 AddSchemaRefs(const_cast<SchemaType *>(sc));
2247 return true;
2248 } else
2249 SchemaErrorValue(kSchemaErrorRefUnknown, source, ref.GetString(), ref.GetStringLength());
2250 }
2251 } else
2252 // Plain name fragment, not allowed in remote schema
2253 SchemaErrorValue(kSchemaErrorRefPlainName, source, s, len);
2254 } else
2255 SchemaErrorValue(kSchemaErrorRefNoRemoteSchema, source, ref.GetString(), ref.GetStringLength());
2256 }
2257 }
2258 else { // Local reference
2259 const Ch* s = ref.GetFragString();
2260 len = ref.GetFragStringLength();
2261 if (len <= 1 || s[1] == '/') {
2262 // JSON pointer fragment, relative to the resolved URI
2263 const PointerType relPointer(s, len, allocator_);
2264 if (!relPointer.IsValid())
2265 SchemaErrorPointer(kSchemaErrorRefPointerInvalid, source, s, len, relPointer);
2266 else {
2267 // Get the subschema
2268 if (const ValueType *pv = relPointer.Get(*base)) {
2269 // Now get the absolute JSON pointer by adding relative to base
2270 PointerType pointer(basePointer, allocator_);
2271 for (SizeType i = 0; i < relPointer.GetTokenCount(); i++)
2272 pointer = pointer.Append(relPointer.GetTokens()[i], allocator_);
2273 if (IsCyclicRef(pointer))
2274 SchemaErrorValue(kSchemaErrorRefCyclical, source, ref.GetString(), ref.GetStringLength());
2275 else {
2276 // Call CreateSchema recursively, but first compute the in-scope id for the $ref target as we have jumped there
2277 // TODO: cache pointer <-> id mapping
2278 size_t unresolvedTokenIndex;
2279 scopeId = pointer.GetUri(document, docId_, &unresolvedTokenIndex, allocator_);
2280 CreateSchema(schema, pointer, *pv, document, scopeId);
2281 return true;
2282 }
2283 } else
2284 SchemaErrorValue(kSchemaErrorRefUnknown, source, ref.GetString(), ref.GetStringLength());
2285 }
2286 } else {
2287 // Plain name fragment, relative to the resolved URI
2288 // Not supported in open api 2.0 and 3.0
2289 PointerType pointer(allocator_);
2290 if (spec_.oapi == kVersion20 || spec_.oapi == kVersion30)
2291 SchemaErrorValue(kSchemaErrorRefPlainName, source, s, len);
2292 // See if the fragment matches an id in this document.
2293 // Search from the base we just established. Returns the subschema in the document and its absolute JSON pointer.
2294 else if (const ValueType *pv = FindId(*base, ref, pointer, UriType(ref.GetBaseString(), ref.GetBaseStringLength(), allocator_), true, basePointer)) {
2295 if (IsCyclicRef(pointer))
2296 SchemaErrorValue(kSchemaErrorRefCyclical, source, ref.GetString(), ref.GetStringLength());
2297 else {
2298 // Call CreateSchema recursively, but first compute the in-scope id for the $ref target as we have jumped there
2299 // TODO: cache pointer <-> id mapping
2300 size_t unresolvedTokenIndex;
2301 scopeId = pointer.GetUri(document, docId_, &unresolvedTokenIndex, allocator_);
2302 CreateSchema(schema, pointer, *pv, document, scopeId);
2303 return true;
2304 }
2305 } else
2306 SchemaErrorValue(kSchemaErrorRefUnknown, source, ref.GetString(), ref.GetStringLength());
2307 }
2308 }
2309 }
2310 }
2311
2312 // Invalid/Unknown $ref
2313 if (schema)
2314 *schema = typeless_;
2315 AddSchemaRefs(typeless_);
2316 return true;
2317 }

2320 // If full specified use all URI else ignore fragment.
2321 // If found, return a pointer to the subschema and its JSON pointer.
2322 // TODO cache pointer <-> id mapping
2323 ValueType* FindId(const ValueType& doc, const UriType& finduri, PointerType& resptr, const UriType& baseuri, bool full, const PointerType& here = PointerType()) const {
2324 SizeType i = 0;
2325 ValueType* resval = 0;
2326 UriType tempuri = UriType(finduri, allocator_);
2327 UriType localuri = UriType(baseuri, allocator_);
2328 if (doc.GetType() == kObjectType) {
2329 // Establish the base URI of this object
2330 typename ValueType::ConstMemberIterator m = doc.FindMember(SchemaType::GetIdString());
2331 if (m != doc.MemberEnd() && m->value.GetType() == kStringType) {
2332 localuri = UriType(m->value, allocator_).Resolve(baseuri, allocator_);
2333 }
2334 // See if it matches
2335 if (localuri.Match(finduri, full)) {
2336 RAPIDJSON_SCHEMA_PRINT(Method, "GenericSchemaDocument::FindId (match)", full ? localuri.GetString() : localuri.GetBaseString());
2337 resval = const_cast<ValueType *>(&doc);
2338 resptr = here;
2339 return resval;
2340 }
2341 // No match, continue looking
2342 for (m = doc.MemberBegin(); m != doc.MemberEnd(); ++m) {
2343 if (m->value.GetType() == kObjectType || m->value.GetType() == kArrayType) {
2344 resval = FindId(m->value, finduri, resptr, localuri, full, here.Append(m->name.GetString(), m->name.GetStringLength(), allocator_));
2345 }
2346 if (resval) break;
2347 }
2348 } else if (doc.GetType() == kArrayType) {
2349 // Continue looking
2350 for (typename ValueType::ConstValueIterator v = doc.Begin(); v != doc.End(); ++v) {
2351 if (v->GetType() == kObjectType || v->GetType() == kArrayType) {
2352 resval = FindId(*v, finduri, resptr, localuri, full, here.Append(i, allocator_));
2353 }
2354 if (resval) break;
2355 i++;
2356 }
2357 }
2358 return resval;
2359 }

2361 // Added by PR #1393
2362 void AddSchemaRefs(SchemaType* schema) {
2363 RAPIDJSON_SCHEMA_PRINT(Method, "GenericSchemaDocument::AddSchemaRefs");
2364 while (!schemaRef_.Empty()) {
2365 SchemaRefPtr *ref = schemaRef_.template Pop<SchemaRefPtr>(1);
2366 SchemaEntry *entry = schemaMap_.template Push<SchemaEntry>();
2367 new (entry) SchemaEntry(**ref, schema, false, allocator_);
2368 }
2369 }

2371 // Added by PR #1393
2372 bool IsCyclicRef(const PointerType& pointer) const {
2373 for (const SchemaRefPtr* ref = schemaRef_.template Bottom<SchemaRefPtr>(); ref != schemaRef_.template End<SchemaRefPtr>(); ++ref)
2374 if (pointer == **ref)
2375 return true;
2376 return false;
2377 }
2378
2379 const SchemaType* GetSchema(const PointerType& pointer) const {
2380 for (const SchemaEntry* target = schemaMap_.template Bottom<SchemaEntry>(); target != schemaMap_.template End<SchemaEntry>(); ++target)
2381 if (pointer == target->pointer)
2382 return target->schema;
2383 return 0;
2384 }
2385
2386 PointerType GetPointer(const SchemaType* schema) const {
2387 for (const SchemaEntry* target = schemaMap_.template Bottom<SchemaEntry>(); target != schemaMap_.template End<SchemaEntry>(); ++target)
2388 if (schema == target->schema)
2389 return target->pointer;
2390 return PointerType();
2391 }

2798#define RAPIDJSON_SCHEMA_HANDLE_BEGIN_(method, arg1)\
2799 if (!valid_) return false; \
2800 if ((!BeginValue() && !GetContinueOnErrors()) || (!CurrentSchema().method arg1 && !GetContinueOnErrors())) {\
2801 *documentStack_.template Push<Ch>() = '\0';\
2802 documentStack_.template Pop<Ch>(1);\
2803 RAPIDJSON_SCHEMA_PRINT(InvalidDocument, documentStack_.template Bottom<Ch>());\
2804 valid_ = false;\
2805 return valid_;\
2806 }
2807
2808#define RAPIDJSON_SCHEMA_HANDLE_PARALLEL_(method, arg2)\
2809 for (Context* context = schemaStack_.template Bottom<Context>(); context != schemaStack_.template End<Context>(); context++) {\
2810 if (context->hasher)\
2811 static_cast<HasherType*>(context->hasher)->method arg2;\
2812 if (context->validators)\
2813 for (SizeType i_ = 0; i_ < context->validatorCount; i_++)\
2814 static_cast<GenericSchemaValidator*>(context->validators[i_])->method arg2;\
2815 if (context->patternPropertiesValidators)\
2816 for (SizeType i_ = 0; i_ < context->patternPropertiesValidatorCount; i_++)\
2817 static_cast<GenericSchemaValidator*>(context->patternPropertiesValidators[i_])->method arg2;\
2818 }
2819
2820#define RAPIDJSON_SCHEMA_HANDLE_END_(method, arg2)\
2821 valid_ = (EndValue() || GetContinueOnErrors()) && (!outputHandler_ || outputHandler_->method arg2);\
2822 return valid_;
2823
2824#define RAPIDJSON_SCHEMA_HANDLE_VALUE_(method, arg1, arg2) \
2825 RAPIDJSON_SCHEMA_HANDLE_BEGIN_ (method, arg1);\
2826 RAPIDJSON_SCHEMA_HANDLE_PARALLEL_(method, arg2);\
2827 RAPIDJSON_SCHEMA_HANDLE_END_ (method, arg2)
2828
2829 bool Null() { RAPIDJSON_SCHEMA_HANDLE_VALUE_(Null, (CurrentContext()), ( )); }
2830 bool Bool(bool b) { RAPIDJSON_SCHEMA_HANDLE_VALUE_(Bool, (CurrentContext(), b), (b)); }
2831 bool Int(int i) { RAPIDJSON_SCHEMA_HANDLE_VALUE_(Int, (CurrentContext(), i), (i)); }
2832 bool Uint(unsigned u) { RAPIDJSON_SCHEMA_HANDLE_VALUE_(Uint, (CurrentContext(), u), (u)); }
2833 bool Int64(int64_t i) { RAPIDJSON_SCHEMA_HANDLE_VALUE_(Int64, (CurrentContext(), i), (i)); }
2834 bool Uint64(uint64_t u) { RAPIDJSON_SCHEMA_HANDLE_VALUE_(Uint64, (CurrentContext(), u), (u)); }
2835 bool Double(double d) { RAPIDJSON_SCHEMA_HANDLE_VALUE_(Double, (CurrentContext(), d), (d)); }
2836 bool RawNumber(const Ch* str, SizeType length, bool copy)
2837 { RAPIDJSON_SCHEMA_HANDLE_VALUE_(String, (CurrentContext(), str, length, copy), (str, length, copy)); }

2851 if (!valid_) return false;
2852 AppendToken(str, len);
2853 if (!CurrentSchema().Key(CurrentContext(), str, len, copy) && !GetContinueOnErrors()) {
2854 valid_ = false;
2855 return valid_;
2856 }
2857 RAPIDJSON_SCHEMA_HANDLE_PARALLEL_(Key, (str, len, copy));
2858 valid_ = !outputHandler_ || outputHandler_->Key(str, len, copy);
2859 return valid_;
2860 }

2897 virtual ISchemaValidator* CreateSchemaValidator(const SchemaType& root, const bool inheritContinueOnErrors) {
2898 *documentStack_.template Push<Ch>() = '\0';
2899 documentStack_.template Pop<Ch>(1);
2900 ISchemaValidator* sv = new (GetStateAllocator().Malloc(sizeof(GenericSchemaValidator))) GenericSchemaValidator(*schemaDocument_, root, documentStack_.template Bottom<char>(), documentStack_.GetSize(),
2901 depth_ + 1,
2902 &GetStateAllocator());
2903 sv->SetValidateFlags(inheritContinueOnErrors ? GetValidateFlags() : GetValidateFlags() & ~static_cast<unsigned>(kValidateContinueOnErrorFlag));
2904 return sv;
2905 }

3055 void AppendToken(const Ch* str, SizeType len) {

3065 *documentStack_.template PushUnsafe<Ch>() = '1';
